## Implementation Workflow

When asked to implement AP2 features:

1. **Check the project** — detect language, existing framework, A2A/MCP setup
2. **Web-search the AP2 spec** — fetch the latest specification for the relevant section
3. **Fetch SDK/type definitions** — get current mandate schemas and type definitions from GitHub
4. **Check samples** — reference official sample implementations from `google-agentic-commerce/AP2/samples`
5. **Write code** following the spec — proper mandate structures, correct signing flows, standard VDC format
6. **Follow role separation** — Shopping Agent, Credential Provider, Merchant are distinct; never mix PCI/PII across roles
7. **Cite spec version** — add comments referencing the AP2 specification version the code was written against
8. **Test with mock providers** — reference the official samples that use mocked payment methods
